        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 25 at 2:33PM EDT until July 25 at 2:45PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 233 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Falls Village,
or 15 miles northwest of Torrington, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Law enforcement.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Sharon, Canaan, Falls Village, Cornwall Bridge, Salisbury,
Huntsville, Sodom, East Sheffield, South Canaan, Hitchcock Corners,
Wangum Village, Ellsworth, Yelping Hill, Taconic, Emmons Corners,
Calhoun Corners, Joyceville, Amesville, Cornwall Bridge Pottery, and
Mitcheltown.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
